{
  "text": "The Chl fluorescence originating from PSII in intact chloroplasts was measured with a Chl fluorometer (PAM-101; Walz, Effeltrich, Germany). The steady-state fluorescence yield (F s ) was monitored at the indicated light intensities, and 900-ms pulses of saturating light (PFD, 5,000 mmol m -2 s -1 ) were supplied at intervals of 15 s for determination of maximum variable fluorescence (F¢ m ). The protocol for measuring Chl fluorescence was similar to that described by [CITATION_1] . The terminology used in this study of Chl fluorescence was that recommended by van [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The non-photochemical quenching coefficient (NPQ) was defined as F m /F m ¢-1. Anaerobic conditions were maintained by the addition of 10 mM glucose, 1 mM catalase, and 2 mM glucose oxidase to the reaction mixture with KCN omitted.",
  "correct_citation": {
